## CSS-Komponenten (IMMER verwenden!)

### Buttons

**Verwende diese Klassen:**
- `.btn-primary` - Primäre Aktion (Teal)
- `.btn-secondary` - Sekundäre Aktion (White/Border)
- `.btn-ghost` - Transparenter Button
- `.btn-danger` - Destruktive Aktion (Rot)
- `.btn-success` - Bestätigung (Grün)
- Größen: `.btn-xs`, `.btn-sm`, `.btn-lg`
- Icons: `.btn-icon`, `.btn-icon-primary`

**NIEMALS:**
```html
<!-- ❌ FALSCH -->
<button class="bg-blue-500 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white px-4 py-2 rounded">

<!-- ✅ RICHTIG -->
<button class="btn-primary">Speichern</button>
```

### Cards & Containers

- `.card-tool` - Standard Card
- `.card-tool-header` - Card-Header
- `.card-tool-body` - Card-Body
- `.card-tool-footer` - Card-Footer

**Struktur:**
```html
<div class="card-tool">
  <div class="card-tool-header">
    <h2 class="font-semibold">Titel</h2>
  </div>
  <div class="card-tool-body">Content</div>
  <div class="card-tool-footer">Actions</div>
</div>
```

### Form Inputs

- `.input-field` - Standard Text-Input
- `.input-field-error` - Error-State
- `.input-field-success` - Success-State
- `.select-field` - Native Select
- `.checkbox-field` - Checkbox
- `.radio-field` - Radio Button
- `.toggle` + `.toggle-knob` - Toggle Switch
- `.label`, `.label-required` - Labels
- `.help-text`, `.error-text` - Hilfetext

**Beispiel:**
```html
<div>
  <label class="label label-required">Name</label>
  <input type="text" class="input-field" placeholder="Eingabe...">
  <p class="help-text">Hilfetext hier</p>
</div>
```

### Tabellen

- `.table-tool` - Basis-Tabelle
- `.table-tool-compact` - Kompaktere Zeilen
- `.table-tool-striped` - Gestreifte Zeilen

**Immer in Card + Overflow-Container:**
```html
<div class="card-tool">
  <div class="overflow-x-auto">
    <table class="table-tool">
      <!-- ... -->
    </table>
  </div>
</div>
```

### Badges & Tags

- `.badge-primary`, `.badge-success`, `.badge-warning`, `.badge-error`, `.badge-info`, `.badge-neutral`
- `.tag` + `.tag-close` - Tag mit Close-Button

