## Laravel Blade Komponenten

### Empfohlene Komponenten

Erstelle diese Blade-Komponenten in `resources/views/components/`:

1. **button.blade.php** - Buttons mit Varianten
2. **card.blade.php** - Card-Container
3. **badge.blade.php** - Status-Badges
4. **alert.blade.php** - Alert-Messages
5. **input.blade.php** - Form-Inputs
6. **avatar.blade.php** - User-Avatars
7. **stat-card.blade.php** - KPI-Karten

**Beispiel Button-Komponente:**
```blade
@props(['variant' => 'primary', 'size' => '', 'type' => 'button'])

@php
$classes = match($variant) {
    'primary' => 'btn-primary',
    'secondary' => 'btn-secondary',
    'danger' => 'btn-danger',
    default => 'btn-primary'
};
$sizeClass = match($size) {
    'sm' => 'btn-sm',
    'lg' => 'btn-lg',
    default => ''
};
@endphp

<button {{ $attributes->merge(['type' => $type, 'class' => "$classes $sizeClass"]) }}>
    {{ $slot }}
</button>
```

**Verwendung:**
```blade
<x-button variant="primary">Speichern</x-button>
<x-button variant="danger" size="sm">Löschen</x-button>
```

